Product name: Deer antler dog chews-free shipping!
Description:
This listing is for a deer antler dog chew. Extra Large will be between 7"-9" in length but forked antlers may be up to 13" long. Large will be between 6"-8" in length, medium will be between 5"-7" in length and small will be between 4"-6" in length. The antlers may be straight or forked. Deer antlers are typically harder than elk antlers, this makes them a great choice for very aggressive chewers. Elk antlers are more "porous", while deer are very dense. Both are a great choice, you just need to be aware that if your dog needs a softer chew, deer are probably not the right fit. Elk can be hard or soft depending on the location on the antler it was cut from, which is why we give you the choice of core density on elk, but not deer. Elk antlers are bigger than deer antlers. This limits the size we can cut from a deer so a large elk is bigger than a large deer. They are priced to reflect this. Note: The photos shown are stock photos and you will receive a similar item. Please keep in mind that antlers are unique in shape and appearance. 
We believe that every dog should unleash their wild instincts and enjoy a piece of 100% naturally shed deer or elk antler. Many wild animals chew on antlers as a source of nutrients. Every year deer and elk shed their antlers so that they can regrow new ones for the next year. They shed them, we pick them up, you give them to your best friend.  Each antler is washed with water to get rid of any dirt, next we make specific cuts to meet your dog’s needs. We also take the time to smooth down all the edges for safe chewing.
Some of the benefits to giving your dog this natural treat are:
	100% natural- no additives, no coloring, no GMO, no chemicals
	No colors to stain your carpet
	Long lasting, which is a plus for those dogs that love to chew
	Healthy- rich source of essential minerals and nutrients
	No animals were harmed to get this great treat. These antlers were                     shed by 100% free-ranging wild animals from Nevada and Idaho.
Satisfaction Guaranteed!!
It is very important to us that you get the best customer service because we appreciate you as a customer. We encourage you to message us with information about your dog (type, size, etc.) or any specific cuts you might have in mind for your dog, We realize that each pet is different and has different tastes, and we would love to cater to their needs so that they can get a bone that was made just for them! Returns can only be accepted on chews in new condition.
				      *A safe reminder*  
Please keep an eye on your dog when they chew antlers. Dogs can sometimes get very excited with a new treat and can get carried away and over stimulated by it. If this happens just take it away for a bit and let them calm down. When they do eventually chew it down to a size small enough to be swallowed please remove it and discard it. We are not responsible for any harm or damage, but we also do not want anything bad to happen to our friends!
Items will typically ship within 48 hours of payment.

It has a relaxing aromatic substance (passiflorin) that reduces anxiety, improves sleep, and reduces stress and fatigue. Passion fruit oil is rich in linoleic acid, which acts to aid in the restoration of the lipid layer of the skin and provides moisturizing and emollient properties that increase the silkiness of the skin. The creams and soaps, which include this oil, derived from the seeds of the passion fruit, provide a relaxing and anti-stress sensation.
It is great for eye area, can be used directly or on the confection of skin products.
It is a great massage oil that has anti-stress and relaxing properties.

BIOLOGY
Passiflora edulis  is native to Brazil, Paraguay and northern Argentina.The passion fruit is round to oval, either yellow or dark purple at maturity, with a soft to firm, juicy interior filled with numerous seeds. Passion fruit, or Maracuja, is very popular in Brazil and primarily used for food, in the form of juices, jams, jellies, ice cream and liqueurs. Maracuja Cipirinhas are almost as popular as the original lime one. The leaves and juice contain passiflorin, a natural sedative, used to lower blood pressure and against anxiety, and tea prepared with leaves has a diuretic effect. The oil is extracted from the seeds, has a high content of unsaturated fats and lots of vitamin A and C. 
My oils and butters are are wild harvested, grown naturally in the Brazilian Amazon Rainforest without any pesticides, they are fair traded and sustainable resources.

I make this with OR without the addition of non-nano zinc oxide. Though you can see the whiteness of the non-nano zinc oxide, it will "rub in" after a few seconds to give you a clear finish.

OPTIONS: 
1) WITH NON-NANO ZINC OXIDE: multiple studies show that it remains on the surface level of the skin and is not able to be soaked in. This greatly increases the SPF of the sunscreen.
2) EXTRA MYRRH/NO ZINC OXIDE: This gives you a slightly lower SPF than the Non-Nano Zinc Oxide version.  It is just a bit more costly due to the nature of pure essential oils. If you're one who is on the fence about or even against the use of any kind of zinc oxide, then this is a great option. 
3) JUST OILS: SPF level achieved purely with shea butter, coconut, and essential oils. Obviously if you are fair and sit out in the blazing sun with this you will burn! But I am fair and can wear this on a regular day going in and out of the sun and it is a great option to help to protect my skin.
RE-APPLY every few hours and after being in water! I will not be held responsible for misuse of products.

Our Vinyl Grading:
Mint (M): This is a grade that won't be used unless the record is still sealed. 
Near Mint (NM): This record shows no obvious signs of wear. A record that looks like new. The jacket may show only light wear with minor scuffing and/or edge-wear. The jacket will not have seam splits, folds, or cut-out holes.
Near Mint Minus (NM-): This record won't be perfect and may show very minimal signs of use. This is a record that may have been played but was handled with extreme care. The jacket may have light scuffing and/or edge-wear, minimal creasing, promotional cut-outs or cut corners.
Very Good Plus (VG): This record will show light use and may have some mild scuffing and/or fine surfaces scratches that may create light surface noise. Light surface noise may be noticeable during quiet passages and in between tracks. This is a record that was obviously played and shows light to moderate wear. The jacket may have light to moderate scuffing, edge-wear, slight ring wear, lightly turned-up corners, promotional cut-outs or cut corners. 
Very Good (VG): This record will show more signs of wear. Surface scuffing and light scratches will be much more visible. Surface noise will be more noticeable. Record labels may have writing, or stickers attached. The jacket will have scuffing and edge-wear and may have seam splits, ring wear, turned-up corners, and cut-out holes. Jackets may also have a previous owner's name or other writing.
Good (G): This record will have even more wear with significant surface noise, scratches, and possible groove wear. However, with all of these defects described, the record should play without skipping. The jacket may have seam splits, ring wear, turned-up corners, and cut-out holes. Jackets may also have a previous owner's name or other writing.

Description:
Soft Pink Plantable Seed Paper Confetti Hearts - READY-TO-SHIP - Valentines Day, Wedding Favors, Bridal Shower Favor & Baby Shower Favors.
JUST A QUICK HEADS UP 4/16/2017)
These soft pink seed paper hearts have been selling out daily!  If we don't have the quantity listed that you need, please contact us as there is probably some on the drying rack that we can reserve for you.  Thanks!
WHAT ARE THEY?
Seed paper confetti hearts are a biodegradable, recycled paper embedded with NON-GMO wildflower seeds.  When the seed paper is planted, flowers will sprout!!
HOW DO I USE THEM?
There are limitless ways to brighten someone's day with a paper that will grow flowers, here are a few of our favorites.
- Sprinkle on a table for a decorative effect
- Glue them to a favor card as a thank you favor for your guests
- Place 5 to 10 of them in a little fabric bag with an instruction card attached
- Include them in a card or on a gift tag to make it extra special
- Create a complete gift kit with a small, biodegradable flowerpot, soil pellet, and planting instructions
THE SPECIFICS
Size - 1" by 1 1/16", about the size of a quarter
Color - Pink
Quantity - You may select the amount the you would like from the dropdown located near the Add to Cart button
SHIPPING
- This item is all ready to be shipped to you today!!  Usually in less than 1 business day.
- All items are shipped via Priority Mail at no extra cost to you.  Due to customs restrictions, seed paper may only be shipped within the US.
WANT TO CREATE A COLOR BLEND?
Awesome!!  There are a ton of colors to choose from that are also READY-TO-SHIP, take a look -- 
www.etsy.com/shop/KaBloomz?section_id=18975642
TELL ME ABOUT THE SEEDS
The seeds we use are NON-GMO and are not treated with any chemicals. We include Godetia, Bird's Eye, Baby Snapdragons, Black-Eyed Susans, Sweet Williams, Sweet Alyssum and None-So-Pretties. The seeds will germinate in varying intervals and with proper care, many will return each year.
HOW DO I PLANT THEM?
Simply place the seed paper in a flowerpot or in your garden. You may tear the shapes into pieces for larger coverage. Cover lightly with soil. Water liberally. Be sure to water frequently (at least once everyday) until sprouts are well established.
WHY CHOOSE KABLOOMZ?
You won't find any paper making machinery here, except for me!!  At KaBloomz, every sheet of paper is made one-at-a-time by hand anticipating being part of your special day!!

Product name: Thick Textured Dishcloth Weaving Pattern for Rigid Heddle Loom
Description:
It couldn't be easier and the results are beautiful! You will enjoy weaving these wonderful little dishcloths on your rigid heddle loom using worsted weight cotton yarn and size 3 cotton crochet thread. The thirsty textured pattern of the cloth is woven using a simple "pick-up stick" technique that will take you beyond the simple tabby weave....and inspire you to experiment with other textures and color patterns once you see how easy it is!
You will need a rigid heddle loom with a 10" weaving width, an 8-dent heddle, and a 12" long pick-up stick (or a ruler can be used) to weave these cloths. I use common "Sugar and Cream" yarn from my local Walmart which can be purchased in cones or smaller skeins. Size 3 crochet cotton is also readily available in many colors at your local craft store. 
This pattern is sold as a PDF file which will be immediately available for download after checkout. You can then open the file using Adobe Acrobat and print the pattern on your home printer. 

Please note that this pattern is copyright protected and may only be used for the purchaser's personal weaving. You may not make items from this pattern in order to sell for profit in any venue. You may not share, sell, or distribute this pattern in any form or in any venue.

Product name: Yoga Headband - Running Headband - Workout Headband - Fitness Headband  - Pine Tree
Description:
*about our HEADBANDS*
We created this {Pine Tree Inspired} headband to fulfill all your fitness hair hopes and dreams. Whether you are running, spinning, hiking, or yoga-ing this headband will STAY PUT.  Whatever activity you enjoy most we have created the perfect no-fuss, no–muss headband for you! 
*what's it MADE of*
Fit NorthWest headbands are made from quality spandex material that we have specifically selected and tested ourselves to make sure it stays put and is comfortable throughout your whole workout. Each headband is a unique, handmade item so the pattern may differ slightly from the one pictured. To prolong life of headband, hand-wash only.
*how does it FIT*
Fit NorthWest headbands are created from a stretchy spandex material so they comfortably fit all size noggins. We suggest you wear our headbands as shown in display picture above-about an inch above your eyebrows. If you are interested in children's sizes we can do that too! Just send us a message.
*about FIT NORTHWEST*
We are Erica and Emily. Sisters born and raised in the Pacific Northwest; former collegiate athletes, late-night crafting buddies, and weekend outdoor adventurers. We tried for years to find that elusive perfect-fitting headband. Our search too often left us wondering, “Why do these things always slip off? Do I have a weird shaped head?!” {Don’t worry we’ve all thought it at one point or another}. We kept coming up empty so one night after we finished up at our local gym we decided to take matters into our own hands and Fit NorthWest was born.
